### ✅ Final Optimized Text (Professional Tone):
> **"Congratulations on your outstanding accomplishment."**

### Why this works:
- **"Congratulations"** is more formal and universally appropriate than "Well done."
- **"Outstanding"** conveys higher praise than "impressive," with a stronger professional connotation.
